# OPENGEM 300-Loop Research & Product Design Queue

**Objective**: Build the OPENGEM "World Dashboard" product — Bloomberg + geopolitics, part dashboard part forecasting — through 300 loops of deep research, open-source survey, product design, and prototype code.

**Mode**: Autonomous, full auto, max effort.

**Started**: 2026-06-06

**Tracker convention**:
- Each loop produces ONE artifact in `loops/L###-slug.md` (or code in `prototypes/`).
- Mark loop complete by checking the box and adding the artifact path.
- Add new loops as discoveries surface.
- Each artifact must be standalone (re-readable in isolation).

## Phase 0 — Strategic framing (L001–L010)

- [x] L001 — Vision statement: "OPENGEM World Dashboard" — what it is, who it's for, why now — `loops/L001-vision-statement.md`
- [x] L002 — Competitive landscape map: Bloomberg, Reuters Eikon, FactSet, Stratfor, OurWorldInData, TradingEconomics, Macrobond, OECD Data Portal — `loops/L002-competitive-landscape.md`
- [x] L003 — User personas: macro-curious YouTuber, geopolitics researcher, sovereign-fund LP, retail prosumer, journalist, hedge fund analyst — `loops/L003-personas.md`
- [x] L004 — Jobs-to-be-done map: 25 atomic JTBDs across persona × time-horizon — `loops/L004-jtbd-map.md`
- [x] L005 — North-star metric proposal: 3 candidates evaluated — `loops/L005-north-star-metric.md`
- [x] L006 — Pricing thesis: free tier vs paid tier vs MCP monetization — `loops/L006-pricing-thesis.md`
- [x] L007 — Distribution thesis: SEO, RSS, YouTube embed, Substack syndication, MCP — `loops/L007-distribution-thesis.md`
- [x] L008 — Differentiation: "publishes its mistakes" + open code + machine-readable forecasts — `loops/L008-differentiation.md`
- [x] L009 — Anti-personas (who this is NOT for) and refusal scope — `loops/L009-anti-personas.md`
- [x] L010 — 5-year arc compressed: dashboard milestones at Y0/Y1/Y2/Y3/Y5 — `loops/L010-five-year-arc.md`

